<br>
Have a few things I would like to post about the raids/events.<br>
<br>
1. Please use the proper terminology when posting a suggestion. <br>
EVENT-  An event is something that is casual. Anyone in the level range can attend and does not require sign up. An event is also a guild wide gathering that does not involve xp.<br>
<br>
XP GROUP-  An xp group is small group (6 or less) of people meeting for experience. Could be two groups even but just there to get xp.<br>
<br>
RAID-  A raid is reserved for camping a specific mob or getting a specific item. It can be one group to many groups depending on the reason. Requires sign up.<br>
<br>
2. Getting an event/raid posted<br>
-Post your idea on the board. Your post needs to include the following:<br>
Purpose (why/what)<br>
Recommended Level of attendees<br>
Location<br>
Good Days/Times<br>
-within 5 days of post you'll see a &quot;EVENT SCHEDULED&quot; post by me with a date...this means it's on the calendar. Changes to Day/Time need to be posted as a reply and I will then alter the posting as a Reschedule.<br>
-If you want the event/raid/xp group in the MOTD you will need to let Jennat know by indicating it in your proposal post. Jennat is the guild herald and will see it get's posted.<br>
*Keep in mind...it is up to you to locate all the information such as the level range of the mobs, dangers, etc.<br>
<br>
3. EVENT/RAID LEADER<br>
<br>
-Be online 45 mins to an hour before said event. It is up to you to get things organized. Arrange people in groups and make sure everyone who is on time has been moved to the correct location. You will also need to provide a briefing. If it is a major event you might post the briefing here 1-2 days prior to. Including links to maps, dangers, links to websites (if you are using any)<br>
-If you are late you will need to reschedule your said event. As being late holds up several people and detracts from their game.<br>
-You are responsible for making sure EVERYONE gets to some place safe at the end of the event.<br>
<br>
3. EVENT/RAID ATTENDEE<br>
<br>
-Be on time. It is inconsiderate to make others wait for you. It is up to the event leader as to whether or not you will be allowed to participate if you are late.<br>
-Porting times are always posted. If you need a port you will need to be at a druid ring or wizzie spires by the said port time or you will not be ported. Ports are a courtesy..please treat them as such.<br>
-Be prepared. <br>
  *If you need supplies like food, water, spell components, etc. Get it before hand.<br>
  *You need to check the message board prior to login for briefings regarding the event.<br>
-Remember.....Attendance is at your own risk especially if you are lower than the recommended level.<br>
-If you say you will attend an event and you cannot it is up to YOU to post that you cannot attend. Multiple absences without posts/notification may result in you being excluded from future events. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub39.ezboard.com/bfellowshipforlife.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jhaydshadetree@fellowshipforlife>JhaydShadetree</A> at: 1/10/03 8:50:16 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=9.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm5.emailToFriend?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm5.threadControl?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/blueMoon/deleteThread.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub39.ezboard.com/ffellowshipforlifefrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=9.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub39.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cell